    "recap_headline": "Baseball",
    "recap_text": "LOS ANGELES\n\u2013\nJack Basseer\nhit a walk-off, two-run home run in the bottom of the ninth to propel the No. 13 USC Trojans past CSU Bakersfield, 4-3, at home on Wednesday night.\nThe USC offense struggled to find its footing all game, but after a leadoff walk in the bottom of the ninth, one swing by Basseer put the home team in front for the first time all night. The Trojans move to 21-1 on the season with the win, while the Roadrunners fall to 7-14.\nMaximo Martinez\nworked a leadoff walk to start the ninth and after a flyout to center, Basseer turned on a 1-1 pitch and hit it 409 feet over the left field wall. It was his team-leading fifth homer of the year.\nThe Roadrunners grabbed a 2-0 lead on a two-run double in the third inning and then made it 3-0 with an RBI single in the fifth. USC finally got on the board with a pair of runs in the sixth, scoring on a sacrifice fly by\nAbbrie Covarrubias\nand a Bakersfield error.\nHenry Chabot\npicked up the win as the pitcher of record in the ninth, tossing 2.0 scoreless innings out of the bullpen without giving up a hit.\nBen Cushnie\nworked 3.0 scoreless frames, allowing just one hit while striking out two.\nTOP PERFORMERS\nJack Basseer\n: 1-for-4, GW 2-R HR\nBen Cushnie\n: 3.0 IP, H, 0R, BB, 2K\nHenry Chabot\n: W, 2.0 IP, 0H, 0R, BB, 2K\nCOMING UP\nBig Ten play resumes on Friday as Washington comes to Dedeaux Field for a three-game set. All USC home games will be broadcast on B1G+.\nShirtless interviews only allowed after a walk-off bomb \u270c\ufe0f\n#FightOn\nx\n@YETICoolers\npic.twitter.com/8XX4HkZdJx\n\u2014 USC Baseball (@USC_Baseball)\nMarch 19, 2026"
